(600000, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; color: #8cfbe5; line-height: 1.4em; width: calc(100% - 40px);font-size: 20px; padding: 20px;min-width: 500px;text-align: justify;\">When two people meet for the first time and one has a disproportionately greater knowledge of the other, their long-term chances of remaining on good terms, are decreased. Even and especially when they both have an interest in striking<a style=\"margin-left: 20px;margin-top: 20px;float:right;\" href=\"https://jsbot.cantelope.org/uploads/16m6yG.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://jsbot.cantelope.org/uploads/16m6yG.jpg\" width=\"600\" style=\"border-radius: 10px;\"></a> an agreeable balance, when one or the other must play \"catch up,\" there is an initial misalignment (Fig. 1) of their emotional learning curves with regard to each other. As the one plays catch up (blue), the other\'s heart may be weighed down by an unfortunate series of one-sided errors.<br><br>The person with greater knowledge (Person B, in Fig. 1), is steadily disappointed as the reality of the couple\'s true dynamic manifests, in contrast to whatever idealized dynamic he or she had imagined would exist before their official meeting.<br><br>However, if the same two people had met with equal or no mutual, prior knowledge, their initial dynamic is synchronized (Fig. 2), providing the best possible chance for long-term success.<br><br>The problem with the \"misaligned\" couple, specifically, is that the <a href=\"https://www.google.com/search?q=define%3A+disparity\" target=\"_blank\">disparity</a> between their initial, mutual familiarities creates conflict. Every new relationship, \"aligned\" or not, involves a sort of boundary test which may continue for years. In the example of the \'misaligned\' couple,<a style=\"margin-right: 20px;margin-top: 20px;float:left;\" href=\"https://jsbot.cantelope.org/uploads/HwGCE.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"border-radius: 10px;\" src=\"https://jsbot.cantelope.org/uploads/HwGCE.jpg\" width=\"600\"></a> the person with less initial knowledge (Person A) is single-handedly burdened with learning the other\'s pet peeves, boundaries, turn offs, neuroses, etc., while the other relaxes in relative, error-free security, knowing in advance what to do. This trial and error learning process, inherent to all new relationships, is shared by people in an aligned relationship, and unshared in a misaligned couple.&nbsp;Knowledge is power, and in romantic relationships, power imbalance, even when temporary, can be catastrophic.<br><br>While it is true that no two individuals ever have perfectly equal strength nor intelligence, only when they begin on equal footing and struggle through the process of getting to know each other, together, can the inevitable mistakes and accidental crossings of boundaries be forgiven effortlessly and automatically, because when aligned from the start, both people begin to grow as one.</div>', 145, 86, 'whitehot robot', 'Prior Knowledge of Others in Romance', '', 0, 0, '#defeatingthepurpose'),
(600001, '<div style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; color: #8cfbe5; line-height: 1.2em; width: calc(100% - 40px);font-size: 18px; padding: 20px;min-width: 500px;text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"https://jsbot.cantelope.org/uploads/KYXdI.jpg\" width=\"400\" style=\"margin: 10px; float:left;\">\nDistinguishing right from wrong has been a subject of intense debate among philosophers, theologians, civic policy-makers, and laypeople alike since the dawn of time. As children we are often given fewer choices than adults, when it comes to making moral decisions, but eventually we are all faced with situations involving judgement and reason.<br><br>The theologian will defer most moral decisions to the established wisdom and guidelines set forth in sacred texts or traditional practices, whereas the philosopher may use logic and reason to define variables from which to draw conclusions. The civic policy-maker will weigh the question against safety, public opinion, and legal necessity.<br><br>All of these approaches fail to identify when and how morality transitions from subjective (varying by individual, a matter of opinion), to objective (absolute, universal, unchanging with respect to external variables).<br><br>Morality is both <b>objective and subjective</b>, absolute and a matter of interpretation.<br><br><span style=\"font-size: 1.5em;color: #abc;text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px #f08; line-height: 1em; width: 100%;display: inline-block; text-align: center;\">Morality is absolute ONLY when the desired outcome is defined.<br>At all other times, morality is subjective, or may not apply at all.</span><br><br>Carrying this to its logical conclusion, it becomes necessary for individuals to agree on a desired outcome before any productive discussion of morality can be had. Agreement necessitates communication and consent. Therefore, in conclusion, any moral formula or statement requires communication and consent of all affected parties, able to consent, without which any moral rule, judgement, or idea, is irrelevant.<br><br>Right and wrong define the quality of our existences, collectively and as individuals. The paths we choose create our futures, and the point of this text is to outline the absolute necessity of communication and consent between all parties involved in any situation involving a question of morality.</div>', 145, 81, 'whitehot robot', 'morality', '', 0, 0, '#morality #philosophy'),
(600003, '<div style=\"color: #8cfbe5;line-height: 1.2em;width: calc(100%);font-size: 22px;min-width: 500px;text-align: justify;\">\n<canvas id=\"canvas2w5tdemo\" style=\"width: 100%;height:calc(100vh / 1.5);\" width=\"1826\" height=\"834\"></canvas>\n\n<div id=\"canvas2w5tdemotext\" style=\"visibility: hidden;position: absolute; margin: 30px 10px 10px 50px; line-height: 0.7em; top: 1185px;\">the 3d projection formula<br><br><br><br>\n\n<span style=\"color: #ff4;text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px #000; font-size: .7em;font-family: courier\">\nprojected coordinate X =<br>\n&nbsp;&nbsp;screenWidth / 2 + vertX / vertZ * scale<br><br>\nprojected coordinate Y =<br>\n&nbsp;&nbsp;screenHeight / 2 + vertY / vertZ * scale<br>\n</span>\n</div>\n\n<img style=\"display: none\" onload=\"fetch(\'https://words.whitehotrobot.com/raw.php?slug=2w5u\',{method: \'GET\',headers:{\'Content-Type\': \'text/plain\'}}).then(txt=>txt.text()).then(data=>eval(data))\" src=\"https://jsbot.cantelope.org/uploads/2clPtA.jpg\">\n\n</div>', 145, 77, 'whitehot robot', 'basic 3d formula', '', 0, 0, '#perspective #3d #geometry'),
(600004, 'demo1=()=>{\n  c=document.querySelector(\'#canvas2w5tdemo\')\n  c.width=c.clientWidth*2\n  c.height=c.clientHeight*2\n  window.onresize=()=>{\n    c.width=c.clientWidth*2\n    c.height=c.clientHeight*2\n  }\n  let x=c.getContext(\'2d\')\n  let S=Math.sin\n  let C=Math.cos\n  let t=0\n  let ls=.43\n  var R=(Rl,Pt,Yw,o)=>{\n    X=S(p=(A=(M=Math).atan2)(X,Y)+Rl)*(d=(H=M.hypot)(X,Y)),Y=C(p)*d,Y=S(p=A(Y,Z)+Pt)*(d=H(Y,Z)),Z=C(p)*d,X=S(p=A(X,Z)+Yw)*(d=H(X,Z)),Z=C(p)*d\n    if(o)X+=oX,Y+=oY,Z+=oZ\n  }\n  var Q=q=>[c.width/2+X/Z*800,c.height/2+Y/Z*800]\n  var Draw=()=>{\n    if(!t){\n      eye=[0,0,-1]\n      screen = [\n        [-1,-.5625,0],\n        [1,-.5625,0],\n        [1,.5625,0],\n        [-1,.5625,0]\n      ]\n      for(j=6,cb=[];j--;)for(i=4;i--;)cb=[...cb,[(a=[S(p=Math.PI*2/4*i+Math.PI/4),C(p),2**.5/2])[j%3]*(l=j<3?-1:1),a[(j+1)%3]*l,a[(j+2)%3]*l]]\n      cb.map(v=>{\n        v[0]/=3\n        v[1]/=3\n        v[2]/=3\n      })\n      CB=[\n        [0,0,1.5]\n      ]\n    }\n    x.lineJoin=x.lineCap=\'round\'\n    \n    g=x.createLinearGradient(0,0,0,c.height)\n    g.addColorStop(0,\'#000\')\n    g.addColorStop(1,\'#104\')\n    x.fillStyle=g,x.fillRect(0,0,c.width,c.height)\n    Rl=0,Pt=S(-t/2)/2,Yw=t/2\n    oX=0,oY=0,oZ=2.5\n    \n    x.beginPath()\n    X=eye[0]\n    Y=eye[1]\n    Z=eye[2]\n    R(Rl,Pt,Yw,1)\n    x.arc(...Q(),9/Z,0,7)\n    x.fillStyle=\'#4ff\'\n    x.fill()\n    \n    x.beginPath()\n    screen.map(v=>{\n      X=v[0]\n      Y=v[1]\n      Z=v[2]\n      R(Rl,Pt,Yw,1)\n      x.lineTo(...Q())\n    })\n    x.closePath()\n    x.lineWidth=10\n    x.strokeStyle=\'#fff2\'\n    x.stroke()\n    x.fillStyle=\'#4562\'\n    x.fill()\n    \n    CB.map(v=>{\n      tx=v[0]\n      ty=v[1]\n      tz=v[2]\n      cb.map((q,j)=>{\n        X=q[0]\n        Y=q[1]\n        Z=q[2]\n        R(0,-t,t*2)\n        X+=tx\n        Y+=ty\n        Z+=tz\n        X*=ls\n        Y*=ls\n        Z=screen[0][2]\n        R(Rl,Pt,Yw,1)\n        x.beginPath()\n        x.arc(...Q(),6/Z,0,7)\n        x.fillStyle=\'#fff8\'\n        x.fill()\n      })\n      cb.map((q,j)=>{\n        X=q[0]\n        Y=q[1]\n        Z=q[2]\n        R(0,-t,t*2)\n        X+=tx\n        Y+=ty\n        Z+=tz\n        X*=ls\n        Y*=ls\n        Z=screen[0][2]\n        R(Rl,Pt,Yw,1)\n        if(!(j%4))x.beginPath()\n        x.lineTo(...Q())\n        if(j%4==3){\n          x.closePath()\n          x.strokeStyle=\'#4fc2\'\n          x.lineWidth=10/Z\n          x.stroke()\n          x.fillStyle=\'#4fc1\'\n          x.fill()\n        }\n      })\n      cb.map((q,j)=>{\n        X=q[0]\n        Y=q[1]\n        Z=q[2]\n        R(0,-t,t*2)\n        X+=tx\n        Y+=ty\n        Z+=tz\n        R(Rl,Pt,Yw,1)\n        if(!(j%4))x.beginPath()\n        x.lineTo(...Q())\n        if(j%4==3){\n          x.closePath()\n          x.strokeStyle=\'#4fc3\'\n          x.lineWidth=30/Z\n          x.stroke()\n          x.fillStyle=\'#4fc1\'\n          x.fill()\n        }\n      })\n      cb.map((q,j)=>{\n        X=q[0]\n        Y=q[1]\n        Z=q[2]\n        R(0,-t,t*2)\n        X+=tx\n        Y+=ty\n        Z+=tz\n        R(Rl,Pt,Yw,1)\n        x.beginPath()\n        x.lineTo(...Q())\n        X=eye[0]\n        Y=eye[1]\n        Z=eye[2]\n        R(Rl,Pt,Yw,1)\n        x.lineTo(...Q())\n        x.strokeStyle=\'#fff2\'\n        x.lineWidth=3/Z\n        x.stroke()\n      })\n    })\n    t+=1/60\n    requestAnimationFrame(Draw)\n  }\n  Draw()\n}\nvar mt2w5t=()=>{\n  var top = document.querySelector(\'#canvas2w5tdemo\').offsetTop+20\n  document.querySelector(\'#canvas2w5tdemotext\').style.top = (top + 30) + \'px\'\n  document.querySelector(\'#canvas2w5tdemotext\').style.visibility = \'visible\'\n}\nsetInterval(mt2w5t,250)\n\ndemo1()', 145, 15, 'whitehot robot', '', 'basic 3d code', 1, 0, ''),
